title: Caramelized Baked Chicken Legs/Wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit or 180 degrees Celsius.
Place chicken in a 9x13 inch baking dish. Mix together the oil, soy sauce, ketchup, honey, garlic, salt and pepper.
Bake in preheated oven for one hour, or until sauce is caramelized.
Could also use wings or pork ribs.
ingredients: 1 2⁄3 tablespoons olive oil (to help it stop sticking to the pan)
